description:
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Clinical Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This advert is linked to a virtual event taking place on Monday 16th November. Please visit our Trauma &amp; Related Services Virtual Event page on the Leeds Teaching Hospitals Facebook page or email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;leedsth-tr.corporatenursingworkforce@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; for further information.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited from Band 2 Clinical Support Workers who are passionate about providing the best care possible to patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Trauma and Related Services Clinical Service Unit comprises, Major Trauma, Trauma and Orthopaedics, Vascular Surgery and Plastic Surgery. We also have a 6 bedded higher observations unit and a multi-speciality assessment area.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be joining an enthusiastic team who are committed to providing the best care possible for patients undergoing surgery and treatment within these specialities. You will receive support, education and the opportunity to progress your career and become part of a highly skilled and motivated &lt;strong&gt;TR&lt;/strong&gt;emendou&lt;strong&gt;S &lt;/strong&gt;team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Come and join our team in Leeds and become part of ‘The Leeds Way’ sharing our vision and values. Our Trust is recognised for our staff engagement, great care and rated &lt;strong&gt;GOOD&lt;/strong&gt; by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust is one of the largest acute health providers in the UK and based in one of the fastest growing and vibrant cities in the north.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful candidates must hold a level 2 NVQ in health and social care or an equivalent healthcare related qualification and have experience of working in a health care setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For all new starters to the Trust we have an award winning, structured Introduction to Professional Practice (IPP) Induction programme to prepare you for working at LTHT. Within the first three months of your role you will be required to complete the Cavendish Care Certificate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will take place virtually.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal chat, please contact Christina Leddie, Matron 0113 392 6107 or email &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;christina.leddie@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Internal care support staff&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; currently employed by Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust, who wish to work in a different area, at the same AfC Band, job description and person specification should contact their Matron and employ the internal transfer process.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;We may share information, as appropriate, that you have provided in your application form with external partners or other organisations help to facilitate your recruitment process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
